not at all surprising. =C2=A0That huge Utah NSA data center was probably de=
signed in 2000-2001. =C2=A0At that time, the typical hard drive as sold was=
 probably 2-4 gigabytes. =C2=A0At that time, it would probably have only be=
en able to store the metadata of all phone calls in the world. =C2=A0By the=
 time Clapper's lie unearthed the facts, in 2013, the typical hard drive ha=
d increased to perhaps 1000x larger, or 2 terabytes. =C2=A0That would have =
allowed that data center to store the audio of every phone call in the worl=
d for a year, maybe much more.And 10-terabyte hard drives are now being mad=
